{"word":"κόππα","slug":"κόππα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n58974\" key=\"ko/ppa\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κόππα</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen>, <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">=</abbr> Hebr. &lt;*&gt; (<title_ TEIform=\"title\">Koph</title_>), a letter (&lt;*&gt;) standing between <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">π</itype> and <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ρ</itype> in early Greek alphabets, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.2420</biblScope></bibl>, etc.; later displaced by <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">κ</itype>, but surviving in Latin as Q and retained in Greek as a numeral <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">=</abbr> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">90</biblScope></bibl>, e.g. <bibl n=\"Perseus:abo:pap,PSI:8:958:24\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ PSI\">PSI</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.958.24</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(iv A. D.)</date>: prov., <sense id=\"n58974.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">οὐδὲ κόππα γιγνώσκων</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg1565.tlg001:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Parmeno\">Parmeno</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1</biblScope></bibl></cit>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}